[2] Italy alarm
Date: Fri 13 Oct 2017
Source: Contexto [in Italian, trans. Mod.LK, edited]
http://www.contextotucuman.com/nota/94246/alarma-en-italia-por-casos-de-sarampion-y-su-relacion-con-movimientos-antivacunas.html


There is alarm in Italy over cases of measles and the anti-vaccination movement. Nearly 3000 cases have been recorded this year [2017], 324 only in the last fortnight.

The situation is of serious concern to Europe: Italy is experiencing an epidemic of measles that not only saw an increase in cases, but also hospitalization of 4 out of 10 children affected.

The problem is due to anti-virus movements. 89% of all cases were not vaccinated, and only 6% had received the 1st dose of the vaccine.

To the 2719 Italian patients, more than 500 cases in Germany and 6434 patients (and about 30 deaths) in Romania have to be added. In the heat of the growth of anti-vaccination movements, diseases that we believed (almost) forgotten are leading an alarming return.

The recent death of a child with otitis due to having been treated with homeopathy and the case of a boy who contracted tetanus after an accident because his parents refused to vaccinate him are clear examples of the damage that can be done by pseudo-therapies. But in the case of vaccination, it is even more outrageous because it not only puts the individual who is not vaccinated at risk but endangers all others, especially the most defenseless.

The obligatory nature of vaccines remains a very controversial issue, above all, by the ethical and social problems that it presents. What should you do with children who are not vaccinated? Should they be left without schooling as Germany, France and other countries are deciding to do? Should we remove custody (and parental rights) from their parents? Should we physically force them to be vaccinated? Many decisions are being debated in the world.

Indeed, the Italian government had no choice but to legislate in this regard on 19 May 2017 by making a dozen vaccines compulsory for all schools in the country. Other countries, such as Germany, force day-care centers to report on parents who do not vaccinate their children.

